<seg id=1> The Hague-based International Tribunal has ruled that three defendants were guilty of committing war crimes against Bosnian Serbs. However, their senior commander has been acquitted on the charge. </seg>
<seg id=2> According to the ruling of the International Tribunal, Bosnian Muslim Firallic was not responsible for the atrocity committed against the Serbian prisoners of war in the Zerabic Camp. </seg>
<seg id=3> The other three defendants were sentenced to prison terms for their roles in what people said the cruel rule in the camp. </seg>
